  "response": "Yes, the Yakuza still exist in Japan, although their influence and visibility have changed over the years. Law enforcement efforts and legal measures have increased against organized crime, leading to a decline in membership and activities. Many Yakuza groups have moved underground or shifted their operations to avoid scrutiny. Additionally, anti-Yakuza laws have made it more difficult for them to operate openly, and public attitudes towards them have become increasingly negative. Nonetheless, Yakuza groups continue to exist, though their traditional roles in society and the economy have diminished.",
